{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χειροτον-έω</b>, <br /> <b>stretch out the hand,</b> for the purpose of giving one's vote in the assembly, περὶ τῶν ἀνδρῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Phocion” 34 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; μὴ χ. <b>vote</b> against the motion, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Deor.Conc.” 9:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —but mostly, <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>elect,</b> properly <b>by show of hands,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 598, “Av.” 1571, etc.; εἰς τὴν ἀγορὰν χ. τοὺς ταξιάρχους.., οὐκ ἐπὶ τὸν πόλεμον 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.26; with double _accusative_, στρατηγὸν χ. τινά 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.2.11, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.50 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be elected,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 607 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ τοῦτ᾽ ἐχειροτονήθησαν, ἵνα.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 28.14; χ. ἔκ τινων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 763e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. ἐπὶ τῆς διοικήσεως Decrees cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.115: with _accusative_ _cognate_, χ. τὴν ἀρχὴν τὴν ἐπὶ τῷ θεωρικῷ 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.24, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 517 (_anapaest meter_); χειροτονηθεὶς ἢ λαχών 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 300a, compare 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.106. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> later, generally, <b>appoint,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.112 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of the Jewish High Priest, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 13.2.2; τὸν ὑπὸ τοῦ θεοῦ κεχειροτονημένον βασιλέα [prev. work] 6.13.9, compare 7.9.3 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>appoint to an office</b> in the Church, πρεσβυτέρους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Act.14.23, cf. NT.2Cor.8.19 (_passive_). \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>vote for</b> a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 297 (Lyric poetry), 797, Isocrates  7.84; γνώμας 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.248: with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, ὁ δῆμος ἐχειροτόνησεν ἐξεῖναι.. πέμπειν <b>voted</b> to send, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.13, compare “IG” 12.57.29, 63.4:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, κεχειροτόνηται ὕβρις τὸ πρᾶγυ᾽ εἶναι <b>it is voted, ruled</b> to be.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.216. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>span with the hand,</b> τὸ αἰδοῖον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Artemidorus Daldianus Onirocriticus 1.78 (cited in 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; χειροκοπεῖν codices).","strongNumber":"G5500","accentedUnicode":"χειροτονέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5495","matchingForm":"χείρ","stepTransliteration":"cheir","gloss":"hand","_zh_tw_Gloss":"手","_es_Gloss":"mano","_zh_Gloss":"手"}],"shortDef":"to appoint, choose","mediumDef":"to appoint, choose <br /><b>to stretch out the hand; to constitute by voting; to appoint, constitute, choose</b> <ref='Act.14.23'>Acts 14:23;</ref> <ref='2Co.8.19'>2Cor. 8:19</ref>*","stepGloss":"to appoint","stepTransliteration":"cheirotoneō","count":4,"_es_Definition":"nombrar ; elegir, escoger, seleccionar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 挑選 (林後 8:19)<br>2) 指派, 任命","_zh_Definition":"1) 挑选 (林后 8:19)<br>2) 指派, 任命","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"chọn; bổ nhiệm","_zh_tw_Gloss":"挑選, 已選立","_es_Gloss":"designar","_zh_Gloss":"挑选, 已选立"}]}